abstract: NFL Roundup; Dallas Cowboys waive quarterback Brandon Weeden in anticipation of Tony Romo's return from broken collarbone; other pro football news noted.
lead_paragraph: Romo, the starter, has missed seven weeks with a broken collarbone, and Dallas has gone 0-7 with Weeden and Matt Cassel under center in his place.

headline.main: Cowboys Waive Brandon Weeden as Tony Romo Nears Return
headline.print_headline: Cowboys Waive Weeden as Romo Nears Return
